%% Diagram: EDNS0 buffer-size negotiation and UDP → TCP fallback
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Stub as Stub / Resolver
    participant Auth as Authoritative NS
    participant Path as IP Path (MTU)

    Stub->>Auth: UDP query, EDNS bufsize=1232 (DNS Flag Day 2020)
    alt Response ≤ 1232 bytes
        Auth-->>Stub: UDP response, fits one datagram
    else Response > 1232 bytes
        Auth-->>Stub: UDP response with TC=1 (truncated)
        Note over Stub,Auth: RFC 1035 §4.2.1 truncation signal.<br/>No fragments — Flag Day forbids them.
        Stub->>Auth: Retry over TCP/53 (or TCP/853 for DoT)
        Auth-->>Stub: Full response over TCP
    end

    Note over Stub,Path: If TCP/53 is firewalled,<br/>large responses (DNSKEY, RRSIG, ANY)<br/>silently fail → SERVFAIL or timeout.
    Note over Stub,Auth: Diagnose with:<br/>dig +bufsize=512 NAME ANY (force TC=1)<br/>dig +tcp NAME (verify TCP path).
